// we need to find count of elements in the union of these two arrays.
// we need to ignore the duplicates

// naive solution
1. create a array c[m+m] and copy the contents of both the array into this array
2. for every element check if the element is present in the left of the array or not. then return result. use flag varaible to break loop.

// efficient solution - 1
// uses auxillary array
put all the elements into a new array and add them to the hashtable and return the size of the hashtable.

// efficient solution -2 
// does not use auxillary array
// simple add the elements of one in the hashset and the second in the hashset, and return the size.

time: O(m+n) - contant
space: O(m+n) / theta(m+n)
